BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Covered: Faculty Author Talks by Javier Arbona-Homar and Bettina N
 g'weno
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260218T013000Z
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260218T033000Z
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51817137369841
DESCRIPTION:Join us for an evening with UC Davis faculty authors Javier Ar
 bona-Homar and Bettina Ng'weno as part of Covered\, a monthly event series
  celebrating recent books from the College of Letters and Science. Javier 
 Arbona-Homar\, associate professor of American Studies and Design\, discus
 ses Explosivity\, a sweeping investigation of the Bay Area’s landscape t
 hrough episodes of militarism\, racialized capitalism and historical erasu
 re. Drawing on archival research\, oral histories and site visits\, he tra
 ces how past detonations continue to shape public memory and geography. Be
 ttina Ng’weno\, professor of African American and African Studies\, shar
 es from No Place Like Home in a New City\, an intimate account of how resi
 dents of Nairobi resist anti-urban ideologies to build life\, belonging an
 d new urban futures amid rapid redevelopment. Covered: Spotlighting Facult
 y Authors in Letters and Science is co-sponsored by the Jan Shrem and Mari
 a Manetti Shrem Museum and the UC Davis Library.
LOCATION:Manetti Shrem Museum
URL:https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/covered-faculty-author-talks-
 february2026
X-SOURCE:UC Davis Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Workshop: Cleaning and Reshaping Data in R (part 1 of 2)
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260219T180000Z
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260219T200000Z
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51818563851045
DESCRIPTION:Cleaning your data is often the most time-consuming part of re
 search. In this 2-part workshop for researchers using R\, we will move pas
 t coding basics to tackle the complexities of real datasets and learn effe
 ctive data preparation workflows. We'll practice how to efficiently identi
 fy potential problems with structure and data types\, and write scripts to
  effectively convert and correct these issues. We'll discuss the principle
 s of "tidy data\," ensuring your datasets are structured perfectly for you
 r analysis and visualization. Then we’ll take a deep dive into the strin
 gr package for text processing\, and the lubridate package for handling da
 tes and times. You’ll also learn how to use tidyr and dplyr to reshape d
 ata and join linked datasets. Whether you're gathering your data by hand\,
  scraping the web\, or importing text files\, this training will help expa
 nd your R coding skills to turn your data into analysis-ready files with c
 onfidence and reproducibility. After completing this training\, learners s
 hould be able to: Inspect data files to determine how best to load them in
 to R\; Identify and convert features to appropriate data types\;Use the 
 “stringr” package clean and extract data from text\;Use regular expres
 sions to describe patterns in text\; Use the “lubridate” package to pa
 rse dates and times\;Identify features of a "tidy" dataset\;Describe the a
 dvantages and disadvantages of tidy data\;Use the "tidyr" package to resha
 pe data\;Describe what a join is\;Compare differences between an inner joi
 n and left join\;Use the "dplyr" package to join two data sets on a common
  column\;and learn where to go to learn more! This workshop is offered in 
 person only. All members of UC Davis are welcome to register. Advance regi
 stration required. Please plan to attend both sessions: Part 1: February 1
 9\, 2026 (10 AM- 12 PM)Part 2: February 26\, 2026 (10 AM - 12 PM) Prerequi
 sites This workshop is intended for motivated learners from all domains at
  UC Davis who want to hone their existing R skills. Thus\, we won't cover 
 introductory R questions during this session. Participants should be comfo
 rtable with basic R syntax\, and have the latest version of R and RStudio 
 pre-installed and running on their laptops. If you're new to R\, or want t
 o brush up\, we suggest you start with our "R Basics" workshop curriculum.
  Can’t attend this event? Materials from prior UC Davis DataLab workshop
 s are available on DataLab's website. Check out our workshop schedule for 
 other upcoming trainings. Questions? Contact datalab-training@ucdavis.edu.
LOCATION:Shields Library\, 360
URL:https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/workshop-w2026-intermediate-r
 -data-cleaning-part1
X-SOURCE:UC Davis Library
END:VEVENT
