BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Workshop: Cleaning and Reshaping Data in R (part 2 of 2)
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260226T180000Z
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260226T200000Z
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51834484260488
DESCRIPTION:This is the second session of a 2-part workshop. To attend\, r
 egister for the workshop series and attend part 1. Cleaning your data is o
 ften the most time-consuming part of research. In this 2-part workshop for
  researchers using R\, we will move past coding basics to tackle the compl
 exities of real datasets and learn effective data preparation workflows. W
 e'll practice how to efficiently identify potential problems with structur
 e and data types\, and write scripts to effectively convert and correct th
 ese issues. We'll discuss the principles of "tidy data\," ensuring your da
 tasets are structured perfectly for your analysis and visualization. Then 
 we’ll take a deep dive into the stringr package for text processing\, an
 d the lubridate package for handling dates and times. You’ll also learn 
 how to use tidyr and dplyr to reshape data and join linked datasets. Wheth
 er you're gathering your data by hand\, scraping the web\, or importing te
 xt files\, this training will help expand your R coding skills to turn you
 r data into analysis-ready files with confidence and reproducibility. Afte
 r completing this training\, learners should be able to: Inspect data file
 s to determine how best to load them into R\; Identify and convert feature
 s to appropriate data types\;Use the “stringr” package clean and extra
 ct data from text\;Use regular expressions to describe patterns in text\; 
 Use the “lubridate” package to parse dates and times\;Identify feature
 s of a "tidy" dataset\;Describe the advantages and disadvantages of tidy d
 ata\;Use the "tidyr" package to reshape data\;Describe what a join is\;Com
 pare differences between an inner join and left join\;Use the "dplyr" pack
 age to join two data sets on a common column\;and learn where to go to lea
 rn more! This workshop is offered in person only. All members of UC Davis 
 are welcome to register. Advance registration required. Please plan to att
 end both sessions: Part 1: February 19\, 2026 (10 AM- 12 PM)Part 2: Februa
 ry 26\, 2026 (10 AM - 12 PM) Prerequisites This workshop is intended for m
 otivated learners from all domains at UC Davis who want to hone their exis
 ting R skills. Thus\, we won't cover introductory R questions during this 
 session. Participants should be comfortable with basic R syntax\, and have
  the latest version of R and RStudio pre-installed and running on their la
 ptops. If you're new to R\, or want to brush up\, we suggest you start wit
 h our "R Basics" workshop curriculum. Can’t attend this event? Materials
  from prior UC Davis DataLab workshops are available on DataLab's website.
  Check out our workshop schedule for other upcoming trainings. Questions? 
 Contact datalab-training@ucdavis.edu.
LOCATION:Shields Library\, 360
URL:https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/workshop-w2026-intermediate-r
 -data-cleaning-part2
X-SOURCE:UC Davis Library
END:VEVENT
