DESCRIPTION:Undergrads are invited to drop into our new AI Learning Lab se
 ssions! Participants will: Experiment safely with various AI tools (ChatGP
 T\, Claude\, Perplexity\, image generators\, research assistants\, etc.) i
 n a supportive environmentDevelop critical evaluation skills to assess AI 
 outputs for accuracy\, bias\, and appropriatenessLearn ethical frameworks 
 for integrating AI into academic work while maintaining integrityShare dis
 coveries and challenges with peers facing similar questions about AI useBu
 ild confidence in making informed decisions about when\, how\, and whether
  to use AI toolsUnderstand disciplinary differences in AI policies and bes
 t practices across fields Led by Student Services intern Rayan Mansoor\, t
 hese informal sessions will be held biweekly on Tuesdays through March 10 
 in Shields Library\, Learning Instruction Room\, Rm. 205. No prior experie
 nce with AI is necessary. Please bring your own device.
