BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Covered: Faculty Author Talks by Lisa G. Materson and Corrie Decke
 r
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260414T123000Z
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260414T143000Z
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51817323649794
DESCRIPTION:Join us for an evening with UC Davis faculty authors Lisa G. M
 aterson and Corrie Decker as part of Covered\, a monthly event series cele
 brating recent books from the College of Letters and Science. Lisa G. Mate
 rson\, associate professor of history\, traces civil rights activist Ruth 
 Reynolds’ deep involvement in the movement for Puerto Rico’s independe
 nce in Radical Solidarity\, offering a nuanced account of political allysh
 ip\, anti-colonial struggle and cross-racial collaboration. Corrie Decker\
 , associate professor of history\, examines how colonial courts and ethnog
 raphers in 20th century East Africa transformed complex rites of passage i
 nto simplified “puberty rites" in The Age of Sex: Custom\, Law\, and Rit
 ual in Twentieth-Century East Africa\, reshaping legal understandings of c
 hildhood\, adulthood\, gender and sexual maturity. Covered: Spotlighting F
 aculty Authors in Letters and Science is co-sponsored by the Jan Shrem and
  Maria Manetti Shrem Museum and the UC Davis Library.
LOCATION:Manetti Shrem Museum
URL:https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/covered-faculty-author-talks-
 by-lisa-materson-and-corrie-decker
X-SOURCE:UC Davis Library
END:VEVENT
