DESCRIPTION:Join us for an evening with UC Davis faculty authors Claire Go
 ldstein and Michael Dylan Foster as part of Covered\, a monthly event seri
 es celebrating recent books from the College of Letters and Science. Clair
 e Goldstein\, professor of French and Italian\, discusses In the Sun King
 ’s Cosmos\, her engaging study of how comets shaped scientific\, politic
 al and cultural imagination in 17th century France. Michael Dylan Foster\,
  professor of East Asian Languages and Cultures\, presents the expanded ed
 ition of The Book of Yokai\, exploring the folklore\, history and ongoing 
 cultural life of Japan’s supernatural beings. Covered: Spotlighting Facu
 lty Authors in Letters and Science is co-sponsored by the Jan Shrem and Ma
 ria Manetti Shrem Museum and the UC Davis Library.
